# Get Service Request Actvity

Retrieves activity information for Service Requests as well as Community Messaging.

## Endpoint

`GET /api/v2/units/:unit_id/service-requests/activity`

## Query Parameters

- `query_id`: string, options. Used for mapping log tracking entries only.
- `page`: integer, optional. Page of results to display.
- `limit`: integer, optional. Number of results returned per page.
- `service_request_id`: string, optional. Returnes results for the identified Service Request ID exclusively.
- `start`: utc_datetime, optional. Starting date to filter activity from.
- `end`: utc_datetime, optional. Ending date to filter activity from.
- `categories`: string, optional. Comma-separated list of activity genres to return.
  valid data is `service-request`, `broadcast-message`, or `service-request,broadcast-message` in any order.

